---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";

const title = "Meta Analysis for One Piece Card Game";
const description = "Weekly One Piece Card Game meta analysis covering top leaders, matchup trends, and format shifts.";
---

<MainLayout title={title} description={description}>
	<section class="hero">
		<div class="container">
			<span class="hero-badge">Meta Analysis</span>
			<h1>Meta Analysis for One Piece Card Game</h1>
			<p>
				Weekly snapshots of what’s winning now, why it’s winning, and how to respond. Scroll for the tier list
				and recent meta notes.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="tier-list">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>Current Tier List</h2>
			<p>
				This tier list is updated regularly to reflect results from tournaments, locals, and major online
				events. Use it as a fast snapshot of which leaders are converting today and which archetypes are
				pressured by the field. When the list shifts, check Deck Guides to understand why.
			</p>
			<figure class="tier-figure">
				<img
					loading="lazy"
					src="/assets/tier-list/Nouvelle tier list .png"
					alt="One Piece Card Game tier list snapshot"
				/>
				<figcaption>Current tier list of decks.</figcaption>
			</figure>
			<div class="tier-article-links">
				<a class="tier-article-card" href="/meta-analysis/monkey-d-luffy-eb02-stats-in-op15">
					<div class="article-thumb" aria-hidden="true">
						<img
							loading="lazy"
							src="/assets/guides/Monkey D. Luffy EB02-010.png"
							alt=""
						/>
					</div>
					<div class="tier-article-copy">
						<strong>Monkey.D.Luffy EB02 Stats in OP15 Format</strong>
						<p>Turn-order win rates for Green/Purple Monkey.D.Luffy in the OP15 format.</p>
					</div>
				</a>
				<a class="tier-article-card" href="/meta-analysis/nami-op11-stats-in-op15">
					<div class="article-thumb" aria-hidden="true">
						<img
							loading="lazy"
							src="/assets/guides/nami-op11.png"
							alt=""
						/>
					</div>
					<div class="tier-article-copy">
						<strong>Nami OP11 Stats in OP15 Format</strong>
						<p>Turn-order win rates for Blue/Yellow Nami in the OP15 format.</p>
					</div>
				</a>
				<a class="tier-article-card" href="/meta-analysis/portgas-d-ace-op15-stats">
					<div class="article-thumb" aria-hidden="true">
						<img
							loading="lazy"
							src="/assets/guides/portgas-d-ace-op13.png"
							alt=""
						/>
					</div>
					<div class="tier-article-copy">
						<strong>Ace OP13 Stats in OP15 Format</strong>
						<p>Turn-order win rates for Red/Blue Ace in the OP15 format.</p>
					</div>
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="seo-block">
		<div class="container">
			<h2>About Our Meta Analysis</h2>
			<p>
				Winning consistently starts with understanding the field. Our meta analysis breaks down what is
				performing well, which leaders are rising, and why certain lists convert better than others. We focus
				on data-driven patterns from tournaments and community events, then translate those patterns into
				practical decisions you can bring to your next round.
			</p>
			<p>
				Expect weekly snapshots of top leaders, the interaction packages they lean on, and the matchup
				pressure points that keep them in check. We also highlight tech cards that swing specific pairings
				and explain when they are worth the slot. If you need a leader-specific plan, jump to
				<a href="/deck-guides">Deck Guides</a>. Beginners can start with
				<a href="/beginner-guides">Beginner Guides</a> to build a strong foundation before diving into advanced
				teching.
			</p>
			<p>
				These updates are built for fast scanning on mobile while keeping the depth needed for tournament
				preparation. You will see format threats, counter options, and the likely next moves as new sets drop
				or the <a href="/banlist">Banlist</a> shifts. Save the pages you rely on so you can react quickly when
				the meta moves.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
	.tier-list {
		padding: 40px 0 20px;
	}

	.tier-list h2 {
		margin-bottom: 12px;
	}

	.tier-figure {
		margin: 24px 0 0;
		padding: 18px;
		background: rgba(14, 18, 30, 0.8);
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 120, 52, 0.25);
		border-radius: 18px;
		box-shadow: 0 16px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
	}

	.tier-figure img {
		display: block;
		width: 100%;
		height: auto;
		border-radius: 12px;
	}

	.tier-figure figcaption {
		margin-top: 12px;
		color: rgba(234, 238, 255, 0.7);
		font-size: 0.95rem;
	}

	.tier-article-links {
		margin-top: 18px;
	}

	.tier-article-card {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 76px minmax(0, 1fr);
		gap: 0.95rem;
		align-items: start;
		padding: 16px 18px;
		background: rgba(14, 18, 30, 0.78);
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 120, 52, 0.2);
		border-radius: 18px;
		box-shadow: 0 16px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.28);
		text-decoration: none;
		color: inherit;
		transition: transform 0.18s ease, border-color 0.18s ease, background 0.18s ease;
	}

	.tier-article-card:hover {
		transform: translateY(-2px);
		border-color: rgba(255, 120, 52, 0.38);
		background: rgba(18, 23, 38, 0.92);
	}

	.article-thumb {
		width: 76px;
		border-radius: 16px;
		overflow: hidden;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 120, 52, 0.22);
		background: rgba(8, 11, 19, 0.92);
		box-shadow: 0 10px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.28);
	}

	.article-thumb img {
		display: block;
		width: 100%;
		aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
		height: auto;
		object-fit: cover;
		object-position: center top;
	}

	.tier-article-copy {
		display: grid;
		gap: 0.35rem;
	}

	.tier-article-copy strong {
		font-size: 1rem;
	}

	.tier-article-copy p {
		margin: 0;
		color: rgba(234, 238, 255, 0.72);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.tier-list {
			padding-top: 24px;
		}

		.tier-figure {
			padding: 12px;
		}

		.tier-article-card {
			grid-template-columns: 62px minmax(0, 1fr);
			padding: 14px;
		}

		.article-thumb {
			width: 62px;
			border-radius: 14px;
		}
	}
</style>
